The device of allegorical intbrpretation is naturally resorted to when it is desired to retain old forms which are felt to be inconsistent with new beliefs. As Philo allegorized the Jewish Scriptures in order to bring them into harmony with his own Platonism, so the Stoics allegorized the Hellenic Scriptures (Homer and Hesiod) with the view of hiding the divergenoe between their own philosophy and the popular religion, cf. Heraclides Aa. Hom. proem. Ὅμηρος ἠσέβησεν εἷ μὴ ἦλληγόρησεν, Orig. c.
